And after that?
French troops have left their responsibilities in Afghanistan (Kapisa and Surobi).
NATO and the US are expected to follow at the end of 2014.
It is time for the Afghan army to take possession of its territory again, and for the Afghan people to decide their future without expecting anything from us.
We have punished Afghan farmers in particular by treating them as terrorists.
And ourselves with our 88 soldiers killed, as well as the wounded and wounded.
The Taliban consist of foreign extremists, former leaders who have fled to Pakistan, but often also peasants who refuse an armed foreign presence, as they did at the time of the Soviets.
