The fashion manufacturer Lacoste lost in China to imitators from Hong Kong and Singapore, who made the famous crocodile look in the other direction.
The Chinese authorities are not aware of any guilt.
The CTMO brand office in Beijing admitted that there had been bottlenecks in 2010 due to too little staff and space.
Last year, however, one had returned from the "emergency situation in the course of work to normality".
Thus, the number of unprocessed opposition proceedings decreased by 22 percent.
