I remember perfectly.
It was a trousers, a shirt, a vest type "gillette" and a jacket from the autumn/winter collection 1971-1972.
"It was a gift from him," says Naty Abascal, one of the designer's muses.
"I prefer him to everyone else because of his great love for women and because he emphasizes our beauty," adds the ex- duchess of Feria.
I like the colors he uses very much; they have a lot of light and underline the face.
The proportions are perfect.
Also the princess and opinion leader at the fashion Patricia della Giovampaola d'Arenberg can not forget for the first time when she was wearing a Valentino.
When I was a teenager living in Italy, I dreamed of finally having the age and the opportunity to wear one of his evening dresses...
At the end of the 1990s, it finally came about.
I bought my first Valentino dress for a feast at the castle of my cousin, Prince Edouard de Ligne.
It was a red dress with flying skirt and a draped bodice with a décolleté that makes his name honor.
"It was a dream come true," says the widow of Rodrigo d'Arenberg.
"Valentino does not depend on fashion, its obsession is timeless," explains this Italian aristocracy who lives between París, New York and Buenos Aires.
Princess D'Arenberg preserves her evening dresses of the fashion maker "with absolute care", "because a dress is not only a dress, but also the associated memories".
